A 67-33 share of the ratio of the day then! New Zealand started the day well, dismissing India quickly and then dominated a major portion of the day, before India came back strongly towards the end. Kane Williamson was the hero of the day, stroking a fine 89 and forging useful partnerships.

Well, the umpires are getting together for a chat. They discuss and then take the players off. Virat Kohli is not happy. The light is not that bad but it has indeed deteriorated. Strangely, no light meter was shown, nor was the light checked. Given that this has happened in the extended section of play, it will be STUMPS ON DAY 2 as well.
EDGED, FOUR! How has that gone through? Full and outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, along the ground and between second slip and gully to third man!
Jasprit Bumrah is back on too. 18-4-58-0 so far.
FOUR! In the gap. A short ball, outside off, de Grandhomme punches it through the covers. Two fielders run after it but in vain.
On middle, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
Way down the leg side, left alone.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short leg this time.
On middle and leg, flicked towards square leg.
Around off, defended watchfully.
Ishant Sharma returns. 14-6-26-3 so far.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Colin de Grandhomme now. Around 30 minutes for Stumps.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! India getting some wickets before the close. Plenty of turn already on this surface. Landed around middle, Nicholls looks to defend but the ball spins away and that beats him. The outside edge is taken and the ball flies straight to second slip. Good sharp catch by Virat Kohli. Ashwin has his first.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
Around off, whipped through mid-wicket for a run.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.

Short and outside off, Watling rocks back and cuts it through point. A tired fielder dives to his right but misses. Cheteshwar Pujara hobbles after it from cover-point and gets to it as the ball stops. Three runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Another flick, another single.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Great shot. But what kind of fielding was that? Tired bodies. Full and around middle, Nicholls drives it straight down the ground. Shami leaps but the ball goes over his jump. Ishant Sharma gets across from mid on but does not even bother to dive or even slide. Ashwin from mid off stops, assuming that the ball will be stopped. But now, has to run to stop the ball. In vain.
Full and outside off, pushed to the off side.
Around off, blocked in front of short leg.
Excellent shot. Full and outside off, Watling leans and flicks it through mid-wicket. Jasprit Bumrah runs to his right from mid on and keeps the batsmen to a couple.
Fired in outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and straight, flicked towards short leg.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, well blocked out.
On a good length around off, let through to the keeper.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
FOUR! A freebie. A genuine half volley, around middle, Nicholls flicks it wide of mid on. Shami does not even bother to chase.
On a length, around off, solidly defended.
DRINKS BREAK. Second of the session.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, well blocked out.
Full and down the leg side, another sweep comes out, this time for one.
Landed outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, this is pushed through the covers for a run.
Full and around leg stump, swept through square leg for a single.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A bouncer on middle, ducked under.
Outside off, blocked solidly.
On a good length outside off, watchfully defended.
A length ball, outside off, defended watchfully.
Outside off, tapped through point for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, defended watchfully.
Full and down the leg side, for a single.
Down the leg side, flicked to the leg side but off the pads.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A short ball, outside off, Watling ducks again.
A bouncer to the new batsman, ducked under.
Who will come in next Colin de Grandhomme or BJ Watling? It is the latter.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ravindra Jadeja, the substitute, gets into action. One of the rare errors from the New Zealand skipper. The ball is a full one, outside off, Williamson leans and drives. The shot is uppish though, as the bat turns in his hand. The ball goes towards short extra cover where substitute Ravindra Jadeja takes it sharply. Big, big wicket. A century was there for the taking.
A short ball, outside off, Williamson rocks back and pulls it over square leg for a couple.
Length ball on off, Williamson dabs it through backward point and gets a couple.
On the pads, Williamson flicks it to the leg side.
Shorter on off, Nicholls punches it to the off side.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Flatter on off, Williamson strokes it towards cover for a single.
Flighted on off, Kane looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes towards cover off the leading edge.
Flighted on off, Kane looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes towards cover off the leading edge.
Floated off spinner on off, Williamson tucks it to the leg side.
Fuller on off, Nicholls pushes it to mid off.
Another one outside off, Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Length ball outside off, this one swings away late on, Nicholls has no business with it.
Good length ball outside off, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Nicholls defends it.
No run.
Flatter and outside off, it is pushed through covers for one.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Flighted ball and on off, Nicholls is solid in defense.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
On off, Kane blocks it.
FOUR! Bad ball and Williamson gets a boundary. Down the leg side, Williamson flicks it fine down the leg side and fetches himself a boundary.
Length ball on middle, Nicholls punches it towards mid on for a single.
Fuller on off, Nicholls defends it with a dead bat.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.

Direct hit and it would have been close. Full on off, Williamson flicks it towards mid-wicket and calls for a quick run. Substitute Jadeja gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
The last ball is worked towards mid-wicket.
Another tossed up delivery on middle, it is kept out.
Loopy ball on middle, Nicholls prods forward and defends.
Quicker and on middle, the batter goes back and keeps it out nicely.
Loopy ball on off, this is hit through covers for one.
Outside off, a little too wide to make Williamson play.
Nicholls has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Angling into the batsman from around off, Nicholls is behind the line in defense.

Fuller length ball on off, Henry is on the front foot as he drives it back to the bowler. Bumrah collects the ball and mimes a throw at the striker's end. Signs of frustration? You usually don't see Jasprit do that!
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
A length ball around off, Nicholls pushes it with an angled bat to point.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Outside off, this is left alone.
On the stumps, defended.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Loopy ball on off, HN keeps it out.
Well bowled! Slower through the air, it lands on off and then turns away. Nicholls goes back and tries to defend but is beaten by the turn.
On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
The last ball is a harmless one, outside off and it is left alone.
Outside off and on the shorter side. HN plays it with soft hands towards point.
Good length and around off, Nicholls lunges forward and keeps it out nicely.
Uppish but safe! Fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls chips it over the bowler's head. He did not chip it, he was a touch early in the shot and hence, it went uppishly over mid on for two.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish and outside off, this is guided down to deep point for one.
The slider on off, HN stays back and keeps it out again.
Quicker and on off, Henry goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
A little too short this time, Williamson works it through square leg for one.
On middle, Williamson goes back and works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Williamson pushes it towards covers.
Flatter and on off, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Just outside off, left alone.
Fuller and outside off, HN leaves it alone.
On middle, Nicholls works it towards mid on.
Good length and on off, Nicholls is solid in defense.
BEATEN! This is on a length and around off, it shapes away. Nicholls looks to defend but is beaten.
DRINKS! Henry Nicholls walks out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket completely against the run of play! Once again it is Ishant Sharma who strikes with his big booming inswinger. It is on a length and it comes back in. There is extra bounce. Taylor looks to keep it out but the ball hits the glove and lobs towards Pujara at backward square leg. He was actually taken by surprise by the extra bounce and then could not deal with it. End of the 93-run stand. Taylor departs 6 short of a half ton. A good innings by him though.
Good length and on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Just short! Just behind a driving length and on off, Williamson strokes it back uppishly but well short of the bowler.
On middle, Taylor works it through square leg for two. NEW ZEALAND ARE NOW INTO THE LEAD!
Angled into the middle pole, Williamson keeps it out again. There is absolutely nothing happening off the wicket here. Very tough for the bowlers at the moment.
Crisp! On a length and around off, Williamson strokes it nicely but straight to covers.
On middle, Williamson gets right behind the line and defends it onto the ground.
Full and on middle, it is stroked to mid on.
A single now as this is worked towards wide mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and on middle, it is kept out.
FOUR! Up and over! Width on offer and Williamson makes Ishant pay. He cuts it over the fielder at point and it races away to the fence.
On the pads, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
On off, defended.
Well bowled again! This is on a length and around off, straightens after pitching. Taylor plays inside the line and gets beaten.
A couple now! Very full and outside off, Taylor squeezes it out nicely through backward point for two.

EDGY FOUR! The trail now below 10. Shorter and outside off, Taylor looks to cut but there is not enough room to play that shot. He gets an inside edge which just goes past the off pole and down to the fine leg fence.
Length again, this pitches and then straightens. Taylor looks to block but it goes off the outer half towards point.
A huge shout but too high! On a length and around off, it jags back in after pitching. Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Outside off, Williamson does not fiddle with it.
On middle, KW pushes it to mid off.
On the pads, this is clipped around the corner for one.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, this is clipped around the corner for one.
The batsman gets a leading edge on that one.
Ishant Sharma is back! He has both the wickets so far and India need another one from him.
Short ball and on middle, it is ducked under.
Almost does it again! Fuller and around off, Williamson strokes it towards cover where the fielder again dives to his left and stops it.

FOUR! 150 up with a delightful stroke! There are three fielders in the cover region. One at short covers, one at normal covers and the other at extra cover. Williamson still manages to find the gap as he strokes this full ball through that region and it races away.
Good length and on off, Williamson stays back and keeps it out.
Good stop! Fuller and around off, Williamson strokes it nicely towards cover where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
Outside off, not played at.
Fuller and on middle, Taylor works it to mid on.
Loose stroke! This is fuller and shaping away from outside off. Taylor's feet move nowhere and he goes for the drive but gets beaten.
Short and on middle, Taylor ducks under it.
On a good length around off, it is kept out.
Well bowled! Bowls the yorker, Taylor jams it out.
FOUR! Creamed! Williamson played one through that region earlier but this is better. Slightly fuller and around off, Taylor strokes it through covers and it races away to the fence.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson blocks it to get through the over.
Length ball outside off, Taylor defends it with straight bat.
On the pads, Taylor flicks it towards backward square leg for a single.
Good length ball coming in with the angle. Taylor defends it towards mid on.
Length delivery on middle, Kane turns it towards square leg and gets a single.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson punches it to the off side.
Jasprit Bumrah is back. 11-3-37-0, his numbers so far.
On a length and around off, Taylor drives it on the up and hits it to covers.
BEATEN! Slightly short and outside off, Taylor goes after it but does not connect. That was a little too close to play that shot.
Goes back to bowling length and on off, it is kept out.
FOUR! Poor from Shami! He has a off side heavy field but sprays this on the pads. Taylor works it fine on the leg side and it races away to the fence.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven to mid on.
On off, blocked.
Now a run! Ashwin bowls another short one  outside off, it is cut behind point for a single.
FOUR! Slaps this one hard for a boundary! This is a nothing delivery. Short and outside off, no turn here and it sits up to be hit. Williamson smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Big turn! Shorter and outside off, it turns back in. Williamson initially wanted to cut but then adjusts and pushes it to the man at covers.
On middle, Williamson works it with the turn towards short leg.
On the pads, Taylor works it through square leg for one.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On off, Williamson stays back and blocks.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson guides it to point.
On middle, it is defended onto the ground.
Fuller and on off, it is hit towards mid off.

FOUR! You need not run for that. Not a soul moved to chase that down. Right from the moment it left the bat, it was certain it is a boundary. Full and wide outside off, Williamson creams it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
The last ball is worked towards square leg.
Outside off, Williamson pushes it through covers for one.
On middle, kept out.

FOUR! Fifty for Williamson! A very solid knock from him so far. He has looked really assured and now would be eyeing a big one. Gets there in style. He steps out and gets to the pitch of it. Whips it with the turn over mid-wicket and bags a boundary. His 32nd in the format.
On middle, it is eased down to long on for one.
Loopy ball on off, it turns back in. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short leg.
Another defensive stroke to this ball on off. Maiden from Shami.
On middle, KW gets right behind the line and defends it.
Short and on off, Williamson pushes it towards the man at covers.
On off, Williamson plays it late and towards gully.
Length and outside off again. It is left alone.
Starts off with a delivery wide outside off, Williamson guides it towards gully.
Mohammed Shami to bowl from the other end. His figures so far are 9-0-34-0.
On off, Taylor keeps it out.
The leg slip is back!
FOUR! Clever! The leg slip is now not in place so out comes the paddle sweep. Taylor plays it nice and fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
Flatter and on middle, RT works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Taylor plays it with the turn on the leg side.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it around off, KW strokes it wide of the fielder at mid off and gets to the other end. First run of the session.
Floats it up on off, Williamson keeps it out.

We are back for the final session which is going to be yet another long one! Also, it is an important one as India need this to go their way or they will fall well behind the 8-ball. Ross Taylor and Kane Williamson will resume their innings. Ravichandran Ashwin to start the proceedings for the visitors. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Another session which clearly belonged to the Kiwis. They scored 99 runs and lost two wickets of Blundell and Latham. Williamson has continued his fine work and Taylor has joined him in it. The pair is going strong and looking very comfortable. India look jaded and out of ideas. It has been a long time since we have witnessed it. Jasprit Bumrah has been lacklustre and that has been a big worry for the Asian side. Virat Kohli will need to inspire his troops if they are to make a comeback in this game. Can India end the day strongly or will it be another Kiwi dominated session? Join us after the break for the final session of the day.
FOUR! Wow, what a way to close the session! Fuller in length and outside off, Taylor unfurls a beautiful cover drive to find the fence. TEA ON DAY 2!
FIVE WIDES! Bumrah digs in a short ball around off, Taylor ducks and it shoots over to beat the jump of Pant. Bonus runs for New Zealand!
Bouncer around middle and leg, Rosco ducks at the last second.
A length ball on off, Taylor stays and defends it to cover-point.
On off, Taylor prods forward and keeps it out.
Once again attacks the stumps, Taylor though gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
On the off pole, Taylor keeps it out.
In the air... wide! It was off the pad though. On middle, it turns into the batter. Taylor looks to flick but it hits the pad and goes on the leg side for one. Leg bye signaled.
On middle, RT keeps it out.
Misread the length there! It is floated up on off, Taylor goes back to play it. He does well to get his bat down and keep it out.
On the pads, Taylor works it to leg slip.
Shorter and around middle, Williamson works it around the corner and gets off strike.
Floats it up on off, Williamson works it with the turn towards short leg.
A good bumper to end the over but Taylor ducks under it.
On the stumps again, Taylor defends it towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, Williamson strokes it wide of mid off and gets to the other end.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a length and around middle, Williamson plays it nice and late under his eyes. The ball hits the bat, hits the ground and then his pad.
On the pads, Williamson works it to square leg.
Floated ball on off, driven to mid on.
Floated ball on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Another tossed up ball on middle, Ross blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy ball on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Floats it up on middle, Taylor keeps it out.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Another two! Shorter and around off, Williamson pushes it through covers and takes a brace.
On the middle stump, Williamson keeps it out easily.
Full again and on middle, this is hit back to the bowler.
On off, defended.
FOUR! 100 up for New Zealand! Shortish and outside off, a little bit of width on offer and Williamson pounces onto it. He plays it nice and late through backward point for a boundary.
Slightly fuller and on off, it is stroked towards covers.
On off, defended again.
On off, Taylor defends.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads but not in the gap.
On the shorter side, Williamson pushes it to the fielder at cover.
On middle, this is hit down to long on for one.
On off this time. KW keeps it out.
Outside off again, Williamson makes another leave.
Outside off, not played at.
Lovely! Bumrah goes wide of the crease and then angles it into the off pole. He gets it to leave the right-hander after pitching. Williamson looks to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, Williamson pushes it towards covers.
Shorter and outside off, Williamson lets it be.
Jasprit Bumrah is back on! 7-2-21-0 so far from him.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A little too full, it is eased down to long on for one.
Quicker and shorter on middle, Taylor flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Three runs! Shorter and outside off, Williamson pushes it through point and takes three.
Another appeal but not given! Floats it up outside off, this one also turns back in sharply. Williamson looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Too high and the impact too was an issue.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
This one is angled into the pads of the batter, Williamson works it through square leg and takes one.
On the fuller side, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
A single now as this is worked down to the fine leg fielder.

In the air... safe and FOUR! Taylor would have been worried for a second. It is short and outside off, Taylor looks to upper cut it but it hits the back of the bat and lobs over the keeper who runs after it. He fails to reach it and it trickles over the fine leg fence.
On middle, Taylor gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
This one lands around off and then jags back in. Taylor looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter and on off, Taylor pushes it through covers for one.
Good comeback! This is floated up outside off, it turns back in sharply. Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. An appeal but it is turning down leg.
SIX! Trademark Ross Taylor! Out comes the slog sweep. Hits it with the turn so the risk is minimum. He drags it from outside off, gets it right off the middle and clears the mid-wicket fence.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter and on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, Taylor strokes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Williamson watches the ball closely as he makes the leave.
Length ball down the leg side, KW misses his flick and the ball goes to the keeper.
Fuller length ball around off, Kane defends it off the front foot towards point.
On a good length and outside off, Kane lifts his bat high in the air and lets the ball sail through to the keeper.
Full and on off and middle, Williamson taps it to the leg side off the back foot.
Length ball around off, KW defends it off the back foot towards the off side.
Shorter and on middle this is pushed to long on for a single.
Gets off strike now as he works it through square leg.
On the stumps again, Taylor blocks.
Gives it air and lands it on off, RT keeps it out.
Floats it up on off, Taylor is solid in defense.
Very full outside off, Taylor squeezes it out towards third man for two.
Taylor is off the mark! He works this one on the pads towards fine leg for one.
Length delivery and on off, it is kept out.
Ross Taylor walks in to bat in his 100th Test. He gets a huge round of applause from the crowd at the Basin Reserve as he arrives in the middle.

OUT! TIMBER! Ishant Sharma gets another one! He is once again the man to provide the much-needed breakthrough. Blundell walks back after getting a start. This is a fuller delivery. It comes seaming back in from outside off. Blundell looks to defend but the ball sneaks between the gap of bat and pad and hits the stumps. Blundell was half-forward there. He needed a bigger stride to cover the movement. Replays later show that the ball clipped the back pad on its way to the stumps. India need to continue to keep chipping away at the wickets. The Kiwis trail by another 92 runs.
Outside off, it is not played at.
This tails back in again from outside off, Blundell pushes it back to the bowler.
Gets some inward movement but the line is on the pads. Williamson works it down to fine leg for one.
Ishant Sharma is back on now!
Floated on the pads, Williamson flicks it to the leg side and retains the strike.
Flighted ball on off, Kane keeps it out.
Another ball that is tossed up on middle, Williamson blocks it off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated ball on off, Williamson blocks it off the front foot.

OHHH! Close to getting a wicket. Ashwin tosses one up on off and it spins past the forward prod of Blundell. The ball goes between the bat and the body and goes over the stumps. The keeper too fails to collect it. The batsmen take a bye.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
One more delivery outside off, Williamson does not play at it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length and on off, KW keeps it out.
Shorter and on middle, it is ducked under.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! Williamson is in his elements now! On off, it is very full. Williamson strokes it down to the long off fence. The Kiwis trail by below 100 now.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for two.
OHHH! This is floated up on off, it turns back in. Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On middle, it is kept out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Quicker and outside off, it turns back in. It is pushed towards cover.
Flatter on off, Williamson keeps it out.

DRINKS! An intriguing session of play. New Zealand have slowly moved towards the Indian score of 165. Kane Williamson and Tom Blundell have been brilliant in their approach. India have tried hard but have not been consistent enough with their lines and lengths.
Yes, no situation but no trouble! Shorter and on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. Blundell initially calls for one but then sends Williamson back in time.
On off, Blundell plays it late. It bounces behind him and goes towards the keeper.
On the shorter side again, TB is solid in defense.
Good length and on off, Blundell lunges forward and defends it.
Back of a length and on middle, Blundell keeps it out.
Good placement! Back of a length and on off, Williamson plays it late, he guides it through backward point and three is taken. Runs now have started to come at a quicker pace.
A little bit of turn there! It is outside off and comes back in. Blundell plays it with the turn to square leg.
On middle, this is worked towards square leg.
Three! Slightly shorter in length and around off, Williamson makes room and pushes it through covers.
Floats it up on middle, this is worked wide of mid on for another run.
One more short ball, Williamson pushes it towards mid on for one.
Shorter and on middle, Williamson goes back and tries to flick but hits the man at short leg.
Ravichandran Ashwin is on now!
EDGED AND SHORT! Length ball outside off, Blundell looks to defend it out but the ball goes off the outside edge towards second slip on the bounce.
Length and on off, Blundell defends it off the front foot.
Short of a length ball on off, KW punches it towards covers and gets to the other end.
Back of a length ball on middle, Tom flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Length and outside off, Blundell plays it to point.
Play and a miss! Fuller length ball outside off, Blundell hangs his bat out to defend. The ball goes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.

FOUR! This is probably the shot of the innings so far! Exquisite! The sound of the bat meeting the ball and the balance in the shot was just brilliant. Fuller and on off, Williamson did not try to hit it too hard, he just put bat to ball, uses the pace of the bowler and strokes it through covers for another boundary. 50 up!
The batsman drives the ball straight down the ground.
Very full and on off, Williamson jams it out towards the bowler.
FOUR! Another excellent shot! Shorter and around off, Williamson hops and punches it through covers. This is timed brilliantly and it races away to the fence.
Fuller and outside off, wanting Williamson to play a loose stroke. KW just lets it be.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one more run. A wild throw by Shami towards the non-striker's end. It is backed up nicely though.
Shorter in length again and on the body, this is worked through square leg for a single.
Shami goes back to bowling length and outside off, it is left alone.

FOUR! Cracking pull shot! We have seen Blundell play a couple of excellent pull shots. He is a good back foot player and that is evident here. It is short and on middle, Blundell pulls it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Shorter in length and on middle, TB looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the body.
Good shot! Shorter and on off, Blundell stays back and pushes it through covers for a couple.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Blundell lets it go. It has been slow going from the Kiwis as the Indians are really bowling good lines and lengths.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Williamson shoulders arms to this one.
Continues bowling it on a length and around off, Williamson looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Angles this one on the off pole. Williamson keeps it out nicely.
Well fielded! Fuller and outside off, Williamson strokes it right off the middle towards cover where the fielder dives to his left and saves a few runs for his side.
On off, Williamson plays it late and towards gully.
A little too straight, it is turned away nicely towards fine leg for one.
On middle, Williamson defends it nicely.
Too wide outside off to make the batter play.
Back of a length and on off, KW guides it to gully.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, Williamson keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is short and outside off, Williamson hops, gets on top of the bounce nicely and guides it past the diving point fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Tom is solid in defense.
Lands it on a length again and on off, TB keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
Shortish and on off, Blundell defends it onto the ground.
One more length ball on off, TB keeps it out nicely.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell defends it out.
Jasprit Bumrah is back on. 4-1-11-0 so far from him.
Down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but misses.
Three! A little too full this time and on off, Blundell strokes it through covers and takes three. It was not hit right off the middle.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
Blundell works this with the angle towards square leg.
Length delivery and outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Full and outside off, Kane squeezes it to point.
Short of a length ball on off, Williamson taps it to gully.
Back of a length ball on off, Kane hops inside the crease and keeps it out to the off side.
Full and angled onto the off pole, KW flicks it to mid on.
Length and outside off, left alone by KW.
Short of a length ball outside off, Williamson cuts it through point and gets a couple to get off the mark.
On the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket. Maiden again by Sharma!
On middle, Blundell works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell goes back and keeps it out.
Just outside off, Blundell prods forward and shoulders arms to this one.
On off this time. Blundell keeps it out.
Outside off, Blundell lets it be.
One more length ball just outside off, Williamson lets it go through to the keeper. End of a testing over by Shami.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson looks to push it on the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the shorter side and on middle, Williamson hops and works it on the leg side.
Just outside off, KW covers his off pole and makes a leave.
On middle, this is worked towards mid on for a quick run.

Safe again! Suddenly, there is something happening after the break! This is slightly short and around off, Blundell looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a little too early. It goes off the leading edge but lands well short of mid off. New Zealand living dangerously at the moment.
Good length and on middle, Williamson keeps it out nicely. End of a successful over by Ishant. A wicket maiden!
Angled into the pads, Williamson works it to square leg.
Fuller and on middle, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
The physio is out in the middle to tend to Williamson. He got hit on the gloves and looks to be in some discomfort.

In the air... safe! Lucky Williamson! Shorter and on the body, there is extra bounce. Williamson looks to fend but fails to get on top of the bounce. It hits the gloves and lobs on the off side. Lands safe near gully. He is in little pain at the moment.
Kane Williamson walks in at number 3.

OUT! Latham is strangled down the leg side! A soft dismissal but India won't care. They have got the much-needed wicket. It is down the leg side. Latham looks to flick but it goes off the inner half. Pant moves to his right and takes it. An appeal and up goes the finger. Latham walks straightaway. The front foot is then checked but that is fine. Good start after the break for the visitors. New Zealand still trail by another 139 runs.
Slightly fuller and around off, Latham keeps it out.
After a cracking pull, offers a solid back foot defense to this delivery on off.
FOUR! Crunched! Picked the length early there! It is short and on middle, Blundell rocks back and hammers the pull shot over mid-wicket for a boundary. A shot of authority. Brilliant.
On off, TB is solid in defense again.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
Just outside off, left alone.
A little too straight, Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Mohammed Shami to bowl from the other end. 1-0-5-0 so far from him.
Close leave! It starts way outside off and then tails back in. Latham makes a leave. It came back in a long way and was pretty close to the off pole.
From around the wicket to the left-hander, Ishant lands it on off, Latham keeps it out.
On middle, Blundell looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg for one.

Cut him into half! Excellent delivery! It is on a length and around off, it jags back in sharply. Blundell fails to negotiate the movement and it goes between the gap of bat and pad and over the middle pole.

FOUR! Off the mark in this session with a boundary! Lovely timing and placement! Yes, it is a half volley but it still has to be put away. On off, Blundell leans into it and strokes it past cover and mid off for a boundary.
Looks to bowl a yorker first up but ends up bowling a full toss. Blundell works it to mid-wicket.

We are back for the afternoon session as the two Kiwi openers Tom Blundell and Tom Latham make their way out to the middle to resume their innings. The Indian players are out to take their respective fielding positions. Ishant Sharma will start the proceedings with the ball for this session. The 2nd session will be extended by 15 mins to compensate for the overs lost on Day 1 due to rain.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

End of an excellent session for the hosts! Firstly, they picked the remaining Indian wickets quickly this morning and now enter the break unscathed, exactly what they would have wanted. Both Latham and Blundell have got through the tricky period and also cut 17 runs from the deficit. More of the same is what the Kiwis would want. India, on the other hand, have not been very bad with their bowling. Bumrah has been a tad short but Ishant has been good. The wicket though seems to have eased out and it is not offering a lot of assistance. Wickets - that's the call of the hour for the visitors. Can they get a few immediately after Lunch? Do join us in a short while to find out.
Another delivery that is wide outside off, Latham lets it be to see off the session. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
On a good length and outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
Full and angling into the middle and leg stump, Blundell flicks it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Length ball around off, defended off the back foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Blundell is lucky here. Back of a length ball around off and middle, Tom looks to flick it to the leg side but closes the bat face early to get a leading edge. It flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Blundell gets right behind the line of the ball and keeps it out.
Mohammed Shami is on! This could well be the last over before Lunch.
Outside off, it is left alone.
The batsman has been struck on the thigh pad.
TB is finally off the mark and the crowd loves it. Local lad, they will probably enjoy every run he scores. On off, Blundell taps it towards the off side and takes one.

NOT OUT! There is a huge inside edge and India lose one of their reviews. Not sure how Bumrah missed that because it was a big deflection. Can't blame Kohli here as he was behind the batter. Bumrah angles this into the batsman. It is slightly fuller. Blundell is rooted to his crease as he looks to defend but seems to have missed it. There are two noises out of which one is the ball hitting the pad. An appeal and it is turned down. Kohli, after a word with his keeper and his bowler, reviews. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
A huge shout for LBW and it has been turned down! Kohli reviews. If no inside edge, it seems very close.
Nicely timed! It still does not get to the boundary though but three taken! On the pads, Latham works it through mid-wicket and takes three.
Length delivery and on middle, Latham defends it nicely.
One more ball outside off, Blundell does not fiddle with it.

Gets this one to shape back in nicely but it starts from a little too close to the off pole. It ends up on the leg stump. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. It deflects onto the gloves and then onto his body again.
In the 5th stump channel outside off. Not played at.
Slightly fuller and on middle, TB keeps it out nicely. Good bowling from Ishant.
On the pads, Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Good length and on off, Blundell keeps it out off the back foot.
Another couple! On the pads, Latham looks to flick but it goes off the inner half through square leg for a couple.
On the stumps, Latham keeps it out nicely.
Angled into the batter, Tom nudges it on the leg side.
Goes back to bowling a touch outside off, Latham once again lets it go to the keeper.
Nicely played! Does not go to the boundary but two! Full and on the pads, Latham works it through square leg.
Now comes from around the wicket, bowls this one outside off, Latham does not play at it.
Again! On the off pole and on a length. Blocked.
Just outside off, Blundell shoulders arms to this one. Ishant Sharma has really started well. He is hitting the right lines and lengths on most occasions.
This one is angled into the pads, Latham works it towards mid-wicket for one.
On the fuller side again and outside off, left alone.

Edged but short! Sharma lands this on off, it is on a length. It straightens a touch. Latham is half-forward as he tries to defend. He does so with soft hands and hence, the outside edge does not carry to third slip.
On middle, Latham gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Like that! Attacks the stumps, still a little too straight though. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Wide outside off, another leave. Bumrah needs to attack the stumps here. At the moment, he is wasting the new ball.
This is angled into the batter, Blundell works it to short leg.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
Wide outside off, Blundell this time lets it go to the keeper.
Shorter and outside off, Blundell guides it to gully. Not sure if he needed to play at that. Quite risky.
That is a beauty! He angles it into the batter from around the wicket which means Latham has to play at it. Gets the ball to straighten after pitching and it beats the outside edge of the bat.
Another tempter! Full and wide outside off, Latham is not tempted and lets it go to the keeper.
Bowls another one outside off, Latham this time does not go after it.
OHHH! Fuller and outside off, it shapes away. Latham is tempted to play away from his body but then at the end bails out of the shot. That is not needed, especially so early in the innings.
Attacks the off pole this time. Latham defends it.
Starts off with a length delivery around off, gets it to shape away. Latham makes a leave.
Ishant Sharma to bowl from the other end.
Drags his length back a little again and it is outside off, left alone.

Nice delivery! This initially angles into the batter but then leaves Blundell. The batter thinks of playing at it but then at the very end, pulls his bat back. The length though was correct here by Bumrah. Slightly fuller.

New Zealand and Latham are underway! On the pads, Latham works it through square leg. They take two, Blundell wants the third and goes for it. Completes it with ease. Replays now show that it was uppish and was not far away from the fielder at short leg.
Third delivery outside off, Latham makes another leave. Bumrah is a little too short so far. He needs to get it up there if he wants to extract something from this strip.
One more delivery outside off, Latham does not play at it.
Starts off with a length delivery around off, it angles away. Latham makes a leave.

Earlier in the innings, India came out to bat with a deficit of 183. Except for Agarwal, the top-order failed to show any fight. Rahane and Vihari however, showed some character towards the end of Day 3 but all that effort went down the drain today morning as the last five wickets fell in quick time. So the target is 9, how many overs will New Zealand take to chase this down? 2, 3 or will they do it in the first over itself? We will find out in a bit.

For the Kiwis, it was the old pair of Boult and Southee that wrecked havoc in the Indian batting line-up. The former finished with a four-fer and the latter with a fifer. They were smart, bowled to a plan and it all went great for them. Jamieson went wicket less. Colin de Grandhomme though did have one to his name.

So New Zealand are probably a few overs away from taking a 1-0 lead in this series! An excellent performance by the bowlers have ensured this game does not last for more than one session on Day 4. Boult and Southee got rid of the overnight batters within the first 5 overs of the day. Pant and Ishant then forged a stand and took India into the lead. The two though fell in quick succession and Bumrah also did not show a lot of fight. Poor by India actually, they surrendered quite easily today. A fight was actually expected of them but they have been bowled out in just over an hour.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a ruppa from Mitchell, the substitute! A one-hander. Also, FIFER FOR SOUTHEE. He has taken 9 for the game. An excellent performance from the veteran. He has really led from the front. He bowls a full ball here outside off, Bumrah looks to guide it down to third man but it goes uppishly to the right of Daryl who sticks his right hand out and low. It sticks. INDIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 191! NEW ZEALAND 9 RUNS TO WIN!
That misses the stump by a whisker! Fuller and around off, it shapes away. Bumrah looks to drive but is beaten.
On middle, Bumrah works it to mid-wicket.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last man in for India.

OUT! TAKEN! A good catch by Boult! Pant holes out. The second new ball does the trick for the hosts. It is on the pads, Pant flicks it uppishly towards fine leg. Boult there, takes a good catch diving forward. The last recognized batter is out of here.
On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for one.
BEATEN! Fuller and around off, it shapes away. Shami looks to drive but is beaten.
The second new ball is now available and it has been taken immediately. Also, Tim Southee is back on!
Outside off, left alone.
Good fielding! Shorter in length and on middle, Pant pulls it hard towards mid-wicket but the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Shorter and outside off, it is slapped towards cover.
Short and on the body, Shami works it down to fine leg for one.
Mohammed Shami is the new man in.

OUT! That is plumb in front! Colin de Grandhomme's first wicket in this game. Ishant walks a little too far across the stumps. Colin attacks the middle pole. Ishant misses to put bat on ball. It hits him flush in front of the wickets. An appeal and up goes the finger. Ishant stands there and has a word with Pant but the latter asks him not to review and Ishant turns and walks back. India are effectively 6 for 8.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length and on off, Pant drops it towards cover. He wants a run but is sent back.
FOUR! Shorter in length and on the body, Pant pulls it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
Shorter and outside off, this is guided through point but the run is not taken.
Ishant makes room again and Jamieson follows him. Sharma works it through square leg for one.
FOUR! Smashed! Shorter and around off, Ishant makes room and hits it well over mid off for a boundary. INDIA ARE INTO THE LEAD!
Shorter and around off, Ishant guides it to gully.
DRINKS!
A bumper to end! It is on middle, Pant evades it.
Fuller and around off, Ishant looks to drive but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
DROPPED! Another life for Ishant! The change in bowling almost works! Full and around off, Ishant strokes it uppishly to the right of short cover but Southee spills it. Should have taken that.
On the pads, this time Pant takes the single as he works it towards fine leg.
Down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but misses.
Length ball down the leg side and Sharma lets it be.
Length ball outside off, Sharma gets beaten for the third time in a row.
Length ball down the leg side, Ishant looks to pull but gets beaten once again.
BEATEN! Jamieson bowls one outside off, Sharma makes some room and looks to go over covers but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short ball on middle, Pant flicks it to deep square leg and gets a single.
Short ball outside off, Pant upper cuts it over the slip cordon and towards the third man region and gets a couple.
Kyle Jamieson is on now.
Length ball on middle, Sharma flicks it straight to short leg.
Length ball outside off, Ishant covers his off pole and defends it off the back foot towards covers.
FOUR! Ishant Sharma is no mug with the bat. Boult bowls one outside off and on a fuller length, Sharma drives it through covers and gets a boundary.
Length ball around off, angling into the batter. Ishant defends it to the leg side off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Sharma drives it through covers and gets a couple this time.
Full and angled into the pads, Sharma flicks it to find short leg.
Length delivery outside off, not in the zone of the batter and Pant makes an easy leave.
FOUR! Length ball and around off, Pant gets on one knee and swings it hard through mid-wicket and fetches a boundary.
Short ball on middle and leg, Pant ducks under it.
Full and on the pads, Pant flicks it to the leg side and takes a run. The fielder in the deep has as wild thow at the striker's end and that allows him to get back for the second with ease.
Full and on off, Pant plays the free flowing drive but finds mid off.
Fuller in length and outside off, Pant defends it to covers.
Full and angled into the pads, Pant flicks it towards fine leg and retains the strike.
Fuller in length and swinging away outside off, Pant hangs his bat out to defend but the ball sneaks past the outside edge.
Full and on off, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and angled into the pads, Pant flicks it to deep mid-wicket and does not take the single once again.
Back of length ball outside off, Pant drives it to covers and denies the single here.
Length ball on middle, Pant fends it away to square leg.
Outside off, Sharma guides it to second slip.
On the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.

A huge shout but this time not given! Clearly going down leg. It is full again and tailing back in. It is on the pads though. Ishant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. He also slips in the process.
Ishant Sharma comes into bat now.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust! Southee gets Ashwin for the second time. India in serious danger of losing the game by an innings! Southee got Ashwin with an outswinger in the first innings and this time the inswinger does the trick. It is full and it starts tailing back in from off. Ashwin plants his front foot a little too across and then tries to flick. Misses. The ball hits him on the pads. An appeal goes up and so does the finger. New Zealand only need another three wickets. They still lead by 31. Ashwin could consider himself a touch unlucky as Hawk Eye shows that is just clipping the leg pole.
Angled into the batter, Ashwin works it to mid-wicket.
Inside edge! Fuller and around off, Pant plays it away from his body. It goes off the inside edge, between his legs and towards the leg side for one.
On the fuller side, it tails back in from outside off. Ashwin plays it nicely towards mid off where Williamson runs to his right, dives and stops it.
Good length and on off, Ashwin keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side, Ashwin strokes it to mid off.
On middle, Ashwin works it to mid on.
On the body of Ashwin, it is worked towards leg gully.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided towards gully.

FOUR! Edged and it goes well over! Slash hard if you are going to and that is exactly what Pant does here. It is short and well outside off, Pant goes after it. It goes off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Outside off, Pant guides it to the fielder at gully.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and outside off, Pant pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, it is driven to mid on.
Starts from outside off, it tails back in a long way. The length is very full. Pant jams it out towards the bowler.
Outside off, it is played towards covers.
A single to end! Short and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Pant strokes it to mid on.
Down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but misses.
A bumper outside off, it is left alone.
Good length and around off, blocked.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Ashwin  this time.

FOUR! Poor delivery and Ashwin gets off the mark here. Southee bowls one down the leg side and Ashwin just gets some bat on the ball. The ball flies past the diving keeper and into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Length and on off, Ashwin pushes it off the front foot to the off side.
Ravichandran Ashwin is the new man in.

OUT! CASTLED! Both the overnight batsmen depart in quick succession and India in deep waters now. Vihari was playing watchfully here. He loses his concentration and sees his off stump take the beating. Southee bowls one on a length and gets it to jag back into the batter. Vihari is stranded on the back foot as he looks to push it to the off side. The ball takes the inside edge and hits the top of off stump.
Full and outside off, Vihari looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground. End of a successful over from Boult.

Huge shout for an LBW but the umpire is not interested. Boult bowls one on a length and gets it to swing into the batter. Pant looks to flick it but gets rapped on the pads. The bowler and his teammates appeal but the umpire thinks it otherwise.
Length ball on off, Pant defends it  off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Pant defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Rishabh Pant is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult gets his 4th and what a start for New Zealand. Boult has been brilliant in this innings with the ball. This time he bowls one a bit fuller and just about manages it to straighten it off the surface. Rahane who is committed on the front foot to defend it gets beaten by the away swing and edges it to BJ Watling behind the wicket. India still trail by 35 and have lost half their side.
Length and on off and middle, Rahane goes across his stumps and pushes it to mid on.
Full and around off, Vihari drives it to find short cover to perfection. A maiden to start off with for Southee.
Full and around off and middle, Vihari plays it to mid on.
Another ball which is bowled outside off and Vihari lets it be.
On a good length and down the leg side, Vihari misses his flick as the keeper collects it.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Length ball around off, Vihari plays it off the back foot towards the off side.
Tim Southee to bowl from the other end.
Short ball on middle and leg, Rahane goes for the pull but connects with thin air in the end.
FOUR! First runs of the day. Fuller in length and outside off, Rahane leans and drives it past gully and fetches a boundary.
Length ball on off, Rahane plays it with the full face of the bat towards mid off.
Length ball on off, swinging into the batter, Rahane flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on the pads, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.
Boult starts with a back of a length ball outside off, Rahane drops his wrists and leaves it.

We are all set to begin Day 4 which could also be the final day of this Test match. The two overnight batsmen Ajinkya Rahane and Hanuma Vihari are out to resume their innings. The New Zealand players are out in the middle too. Trent Boult will start with the ball for the hosts and Rahane to face the first ball of the day.

Hello and welcome to Day 4 of the first Test between New Zealand and India. The moving day, i.e., Day 3 belonged to the hosts who have managed to get the top 4 Indian batters. New Zealand will look to pick up the rest of the wickets as quickly as possible and keep India to a minimal score. India, on the other hand, have two of their most defensively astute batters out in the middle. The pair of Rahane and Vihari managed to see off the day and their first aim in the morning will be to wipe out the deficit without any further more damage. It is said that the best days to bat in New Zealand in a Test match are Day 4 and 5 so will India finally put on a better display with the willow in this Test or will it be New Zealand who will run away with it?
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

In reply, India once again lost an early wicket. Agarwal and Pujara then surged a fightback but the two along with Kohli fell after getting starts. Post that, Rahane and Vihari have shown grit and have really battled hard out there. They have consumed 118 balls so far to stitch a 31-run stand. That though was the demand of the hour as they needed to hang in there. The visitors still trail by another 39 runs and their first aim on Day 4 will be to wipe off the deficit without losing any more wickets. Can they do so? New Zealand are not going to make it easy for them. Do join us at 1130 local (2230 GMT, Previous day) for what could also be the final day of the game.

An excellent day for the hosts! They are in the driver's seat in this game! Right from Day 1, they have been the dominant side and it continues to be that way. The only moment India had a sniff in this game was today morning when they got rid of Southee and Watling in quick succession. However, it was all New Zealand after that. Colin de Grandhomme along with Kyle Jamieson and Ajaz Patel built a few handy stands. To make matters worse for India, Trent Boult also played an outstanding cameo towards the end which took their lead close to the 200-run mark.
FOUR! A boundary on the last ball of the day. Jamieson goes short and wide outside off, Vihari cuts it square on the off side and gets a boundary. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Length ball down the leg side, Vihari leaves it alone.
Short ball on middle, HV lets it be.

OHH! Excitement among the Kiwi players. Jamieson bowls one short of a length delivery and it rears up on Vihari who looks to defend but gets it off the gloves towards leg gully. It doesn't carry to the fielder. Would not have mattered though as the bottom hand was off the handle when the ball made contact.
Another one which is bowled down the leg side and Vihari does not fiddle with it.
Length ball down the leg side and Vihari lets it go.
On a good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot.
Length ball on middle, Rahane flicks it to the leg side.
Full and outside off, Rahane strokes it through cover-point and takes a single.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Rahane blocks it.
Length ball on leg, Rahane keeps it out on the leg side and scampers for a run.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Short of a length ball on off, Rahane taps it to covers.
Short ball on off, Rahane ducks under it.

Good length ball on off, Vihari blocks it off the back foot.
Another full ball on the pads, Vihari flicks it towards mid on.
Full ball on the pads, Vihari strokes it to mid on.
Short of a length ball on middle, Vihari hops and keeps it out on the leg side.
Length ball on off, defended off the front foot towards the off side.
Fuller length ball outside off, Vihari keeps it out.
Shortish and outside off, Rahane looks to play the upper cut but misses.
On off, Vihari plays it late through point for one.
Angled into the off pole, Vihari keeps it out.
Shortish in length. Vihari evades it.
Fuller and on off, it is driven back to the bowler.
Short one outside off, the batter evades it.
A halt in play as Vihari seems to have an issue with his shoulder. The physio is out.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.

A direct hit would have been close. Southee bowls one on a length and around off, Vihari strokes it to mid off and hares for a run. Williamson there has a shy at the bowler's end but he misses it. A run is taken in the end.
Another ball on off, this time Vihari defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Vihari keeps it out off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Absolute ripper from Southee! He bowls it fuller  and around off, Vihari is committed to defend that off the front foot. The ball at the last moment seams away past the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this is defended nicely.
On the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Nice controlled shot again. It is short and outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and plays it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! A much-needed boundary! Short and outside off, Rahane cuts it well over the point fielder and bags a boundary. India trail by another 52.
Wide outside off, Vihari watches the ball as he leaves it for the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Vihari shoulders arms to it.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls it through mid-wicket and gets a single. First run after 33 balls.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot once again.
Length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Rahane lets it be.
A short one to end! Vihari sways away from it.
Outside off, not played at again.
Played down the wrong line! Fuller and around off, Vihari looks to drive but does so inside the line. Gets beaten.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari keeps it out.
Outside off again but it is left alone again.
Good length and just outside off, it is left alone.
Kyle Jamieson is back on.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Length ball down the leg side and Rahane leaves it alone.
Rahane blocks this length ball on off from with in the crease.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.

OHH! Rahane gets hit on the helmet. Back of a length ball on middle, Rahane goes for the pull but completely loses the sight of the ball. The ball hits his helmet in the end. Colin de Grandhomme comes from short leg to inquire about his well being. Southee too inquires and Rahane shakes his head. The physio comes in and Rahane is ready to resume his innings.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the front foot.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari guides it towards point. He wants a run but then decides against it.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Short and outside off, it is evaded.
Fuller and on off, Rahane drives towards extra cover.
Full and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On a length again and around off, kept out.
Shorter and on off, Rahane pushes it towards cover.
Lovely delivery! Gets it to angle into the batter and then it pitches and moves away. Rahane looks to defend but misses.
Outside off, not played at.
Tim Southee is back on.
Length ball outside off, HV lets it go through to the keeper.
Outside off, not played at.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
One more ball on a good length. It is kept out.
On a good length around off, Vihari keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good running! Shorter in length and on off, Vihari drops it on the off side and takes one.
On the fuller side on off, Vihari strokes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari stays back and keeps it out nicely.
Shorter and on middle, this is tucked towards square leg.
Good length and on off, blocked.
A sharp bumper on middle, Vihari evades it.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side and gets to the other end.
Outside off, Vihari leaves it for the keeper.
On a good length and on off, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on middle, Rahane looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and rolls towards fine leg. The batters take a single.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it right under his eyes.
Length ball outside off, Rahane is happy to let that go.
FOUR! Tickled fine! On the pads, Vihari works it nice and fine on the leg side for a boundary.
Shorter and around off, defended.
Shorter in length and around middle, Rahane pulls. The fielder at mid-wicket makes a half stop. A single taken.
This is outstanding stuff! The last one came back in, this one is angled away from the off pole. Rahane hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Fuller and around off, it tails back in. Rahane plays it towards mid on.

Almost a collision! Fuller and around off, Vihari strokes it towards mid off. The batters set off. Rahane and Vihari almost run into each other but they change directions in the end. Also, luckily for them, Williamson had to dive to stop the ball or he would have had a chance.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Rahane guides it through point and gets a couple.

Another appeal and this time it is for LBW. De Grandhomme bowls one on a length and on off, Rahane looks to defend it but he fails to lay bat on ball. The ball strikes him high on the pads. The bowler appeals desperately but the umpire once again shakes the head.

Huge appeal for a caught behind down the leg side but the umpire is unmoved. De Grandhomme bowls one down the leg side and Rahane misses the flick. The keeper collects it and appeals. The umpire says not out. New Zealand have no reviews left.
Length and on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot.

DRINKS! An engrossing hour of play. Great to see two good teams fighting it out. India started well with Agarwal and Kohli but Agarwal's stay was cut short when he edged one down the leg side. Kohli was looking to settle down but he played a shot to the ball which could have been left alone. New Zealand have the upper hand at this stage and they would look to get a couple of wickets more before Stumps.
Short ball once again and Vihari sits under it.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side.
Length ball around off, Vihari blocks it off the back foot.
Short ball on middle, Vihari ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Length ball going down the leg side, Vihari flicks it and the ball goes on the bounce to the keeper who collects it by diving to his left.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
One more ball outside off, it is not played at.
On the fuller side, Vihari drives it towards the fielder at covers. He makes a good stop diving to his right.
One more delivery around off, it is defended nicely.
Outside off, it is left alone.

NOT OUT! It indeed is going down leg. Poor review from the Kiwis! They are now left with no reviews. It is full and around leg stump. Vihari misses the flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. The Kiwis review. Replays roll in and they show the on-field call is the right one.
Howzzattt? An appeal for an LBW has been turned down. New Zealand review. It looks like it is slipping down leg.
On middle, Vihari works it towards mid-wicket.
One more bumper, it is ducked under.
On off, Vihari keeps it out.

Isn't Vihari watching from the dressing room? Didn't he see Pujara's wicket. It is not a good option leaving Boult's deliveries especially when he is bowling from around the wicket. This time he gets away with it as the ball goes agonizingly close past the off pole.
Hanuma Vihari is the new man to the crease. He replaces his skipper in the middle.

OUT! TAKEN! New Zealand are over the moon! Kane Williamson take a bow, Trent Boult take a bow! He was brought back into the attack for this very reason. They needed either of the Indian skipper or the vice captain and Boult has got the big fish, the Indian skipper. Boult comes steaming in from around the wicket and bangs it short. Kohli looks to pull but the ball kisses the gloves and goes into the gloves of the keeper. An appeal and up goes the finger. Once again Kohli fails to make an impact on this tour. India trail by 70. New Zealand will be hoping for a few more wickets before Stumps!
Fuller and on off, Kohli strokes it to covers.
Trent Boult is back on! He has two wickets so far but New Zealand will love it if he can get one of these two.
Another ball that is on a length and on off, Rahane keeps it out off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, width on offer too. Rahane frees his arms and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Another ball that is on the pads, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.

Down the leg side, Kohli lets it go.

Good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it to square leg and takes a run. The keeper runs to that side and has a shy at the striker's end but misses it.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and on middle and leg, Kohli flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Colin de Grandhomme is back on.
One more short ball, Rahane keeps it out.
FOUR! Up and over! Ajinkya Rahane won't back down. He will play his shots. This is a clever shot though. It is short and angling away from off. Rahane cuts it over point and bags a boundary.
One more short ball, Rahane this time looks to pull but misses.
Short in length outside off, Rahane evades it awkwardly.
Down the leg side, it has been left alone.

Another short ball on the body. Kohli hops and keeps it out.
Way down the leg side, Kohli lets it be. Not wided.
A short one and on middle, Kohli ducks under it.
Shorter in length and on the body, Kohli works it towards the leg gully fielder.
One more short one on middle, Kohli hops and keeps it out.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
Some chin music but the line is down the leg side, Rahane ducks under it.
Length and outside off, Rahane cuts it straight to point.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it on the leg side and gets to the other end.
Length and on off, Kohli keeps it out off the front foot.
FOUR! Virat plays his trademark cover drive. Full and around off, Kohli takes a stride forward and then drives it crisply through covers for a boundary. 100 up for India!
Length and outside off, left alone by Kohli.
Another bumper on middle, it is ducked under.
A short ball to welcome Rahane. He defends it out.
Ajinkya Rahane is the new man in.

OUT! India lose their one of the two reviews as there is a spike when the ball passes the bat and Agarwal is a goner! I'll write it once again, not sure why he reviewed, he has a puzzled look on his face as he walks back but that sound could have been nothing but of the edge as the bat was not even close to touching the ground. A soft dismissal in the end. It is a full ball down the leg side, Agarwal looks to flick. There is a tickle on it. Watling takes it and appeals. Up goes the finger. Agarwal stands there for a minute, not sure why? He then starts walking. Kohli stops him and has a word. Mayank then signals the 'T'. Time for the replays and they show that the on-field call is the right one. A good innings by Agarwal comes to an end but India needed him to stay longer. They are in trouble now as they trail by another 87!
The replays roll in! Hot Spot has found nothing but Snicko is showing a spike. Mayank will have to go.

With just the one second left, Agarwal has reviewed. He has been given out caught behind. Not sure why he did not review immediately if he was ultimately going to review, You would obviously know if you have hit it or not.
Short and on leg, Agarwal lets it be.
Southee goes short and on middle and leg, Agarwal goes for the pull but fails to get any wood behind the ball.
Length and on off, defended off the back foot towards the leg side.
Outside off again, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
One more delivery outside off, it is not played at.
Angled into the off pole. Kohli lunges and keeps it out.
A little too short and a little too wide. Left alone.
One more ball outside off, left alone.
Outside off and on a length. Not played at.
Length ball down the leg side, Agarwal does not fiddle with it.
FOUR! That's pulled with disdain. Short ball on middle and leg, Agarwal rides the bounce and pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
Short and on middle, Agarwal lets it be.
Short ball on the hips, Agarwal looks to flick it to the leg side. The ball lobs behind off the thigh pad where the keeper collects it by putting in a dive.
Length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it off the back foot.
A short one on the body, Agarwal evades it.

Uppish again but on the bounce! Fuller and on off, Kohli drives but fails to keep it down. It does not carry to mid off.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.
A short ball, Kohli ducks under it.
Shorter and outside off, Kohli lets it be.

Shorter in length and on the body, it is pulled down to fine leg for one.
On the pads, this time he works it nicely through square leg for one.

EDGY FOUR! Kohli is living dangerously here. This is full and it is moving away from around off. Kohli looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early. He gets a leading edge which goes between widish first slip and gully and down to the third man fence.
Outside off again, it is left alone.
Good length and on off, Kohli defends it.
One more back of a length ball around off, Agarwal guides it towards point. Kohli wants a run but is sent back by his partner.
One more delivery on a length outside off. Left alone.
A short one now and MA ducks under it.

Edged but short! Good stop in the end! Back of a length around off, Agarwal plays a touch away from his body. It goes off the outside edge but falls short of Nicholls at gully who dives to his left and stops it.
Good length and on off, Agarwal guides it to point.
Loose stroke! Short and wide outside off, Agarwal goes after it away from his body but gets beaten.
Kyle Jamieson is back on now.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
A little too straight this time, Kohli works it through square leg for two. The trail is now under 100!
FOUR! In the air but in the gap! Full and outside off, it swings away further. Kohli strokes it, it goes uppishly past short cover and cover and into the fence.
On a length and angling into Kohli. He pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.

We are back for the final session of Day 3. Indian skipper, Virat Kohli is the new man in to partner Mayank Agarwal in the middle. New Zealand players are all set to begin the session as Tim Southee starts to bowl.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

A wicket right at the end of the session means it is the Kiwis who will be pleased with how things have gone! They got rid of Shaw early on but then Agarwal and Pujara grinded hard out there. The two added a 51-run stand. However, just at the stroke of the break Boult strikes to get his second. He has been the best bowler for the hosts so far. New Zealand will hope he gets more support from the other end. India, on the other hand, need their skipper to fire and Agarwal to continue. They would hope to go wicket-less in the last session. Can they do so? We will find out in a while.

OUT! KABOOM! A wicket just at the stroke of Tea! We saw a wicket on the first ball of the first session and now a wicket of the last ball of the second session. This is poor from Pujara. An error there by him. Can't leave a ball bowled by a left-arm seamer who is tailing the ball back in and bowling from around the wicket. Also, it was not that far away from the off pole to begin with. Pujara does not cover his off pole and shoulders arms to it. The ball finds the stumps. Boult is pumped up and this is exactly what the Kiwis needed. End of a stand which was looking solid. Pujara's poor run in New Zealand continues. He walks back and along with the rest of the players as IT IS TEA ON DAY 3 AND INDIA TRAIL BY 105!
Length ball on off, Pujara keeps it out off the front foot.
Short ball on middle and leg, Pujara ducks under it.
Outside off, Pujara plays it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Pujara blocks it off the front foot towards covers.
Full and on  off, Pujara defends it to mid on off the front foot.

FOUR! Fifty for Agarwal, his 4th in Tests! Another good knock from him. Showed promise in the first innings and doing well in the second as well. Gets there by sweeping this ball on the leg stump fine towards the fine leg fence. He needs to keep going now.
Turn and bounce! It lands on middle, and then turns away. There is also extra bounce. Agarwal looks to defend but gets hit on the body.
One more short ball, Pujara ducks under it with ease.
Close! That came back in sharply. Behind a length and outside off. It comes back in late. Pujara looks to keep it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Shortish and on the body, Pujara works it towards square leg.
A short one on the body, Pujara ducks under it.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
SIX! Floated ball on middle and off, Agarwal dances down the track and lofts it over the bowler for maximum at long off.
Floated ball on off, Agarwal taps it to point.
FOUR! Flatter and shorter on middle, Agarwal rocks onto the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up ball on off, Agarwal plays it to point.
Full ball down the leg side, Agarwal defends it to short leg.

Full and on the pads, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bumper! Pujara lets it sail over him.

Replays roll in but from the first one it is very difficult to decide whether it is the arm guard or the glove. Hot Spot then shows a mark on the arm guard. Some more replays are seen but the umpire does not find anything conclusive to overturn the on-field decision so New Zealand end up losing their review.
A huge appeal for a caught behind has been turned down! New Zealand review. Not sure what it was off, it looked like the arm guard.
